{
  "texts": [
    "In our results, the F1 score captures this impact together with other possible factors like for example the effectiveness of the pre-processing.Hallucinations leading to non-compliant outputs never occurred with the advanced models we adopted in our experiments, while they may occur when using simpler and smaller LLMs (as we previously discussed in Section 5.2).",
    "To avoid this problem, a test can be added to check whether the output activity is in the required set and, if necessary, ask the LLM to correct its prediction.In general, hallucination mitigation actions can be taken.",
    "For example, the ADL-LLM's system prompt adopts the Chain of Thought (CoT) that is known to mitigate the problem, even though we did not observe an advantage in terms of recognition rates in our experiments besides improving interpretability.",
    "Few-shot prompting also reduces the risk of hallucination.",
    "In future work, we will explore alternative approaches (e.g., ensembles of different LLMs)."
  ]
}